The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, April 06, 2004 				 Cheap shares for IPCL employees
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, April 5: The government is offering over 1.24 crore shares to the employees of Indian Petrochemicals Corporation Ltd (IPCL) at Rs 57 apiece, more than a month after its residual stake sale offer.																								IPCL today informed the stock exchanges that this follows the shareholders agreement on June 4, 2002, between the government and Reliance Petroinvestments Ltd.																								At Rs 57 per share, the government is giving away the stock at one-third the price set for the public in its stake sale offer. The entire offer price of Rs 57 per share is payable as application money, it added.																								However, these shares are subject to a lock-in period of three years from the date of allotment. The offer opens on April 12 and closes on April 21.																								The IPCL scrip opened at Rs 193 on the Bombay Stock Exchange, struck an intra-day high of Rs 200.35 and ended at Rs 194. 
